name: Rage
description:
rage
noun 
\ ˈrāj

Definition of rage

1a : violent and uncontrolled anger 
b : a fit of violent wrath 
c archaic : insanity 
2 : violent action (as of wind or sea) 
3 : an intense feeling : passion 
4 : a fad pursued with intense enthusiasm was all the rage 
rage

Definition of rage
intransitive verb
1 : to be in a rage 
2 : to be in tumult
